first ensure Node.js (v18 or above) and pnpm are installed on your system, then clone the repository and navigate into the project folder, run pnpm install to install all dependencies, create a .env.local file in the root directory and add your Airtable credentials (AIRTABLE_API_KEY, AIRTABLE_BASE_ID, and optionally AIRTABLE_TABLE_NAME=RSVPs), make sure your Airtable table contains the columns Email, Status, and Submitted At, restart the server after adding environment variables, and finally start the application using pnpm dev and open http://localhost:3000 in your browser to view and test the RSVP form.